The paper deals with multi-objective optimization, which is a topic that falls under machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of bandits and user feedback also suggests a focus on reinforcement learning and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
